args:
Catherine and Eugene have a falling-out over
the creature called Sam—but after Catherine
takes the creature to her home, he disappears.
As the prince runs into the pair searching for
Sam, word comes of an incoming fiend attack.
What in heaven's name IS this creature?!\nIt's so...so...
Get away from it, lady!\nYour stupidity is contagious.
I resolutely refuse! Also, how very bold\nof you to call ME stupid when you are\nnaught but a mewling little craven.
You are SO annoying, gosh! Listen up:\nIf you get all carried away with this,\nI'm not responsible for what happens.
*sigh* Ahem! Yes, well, as shocking as\nthis will be to hear, I fear I may have let\nmyself get a touch carried away there.
So what IS this little thing, mmm?\nI've never seen a creature like it.
Dunno. But it looked like a Sam,\nso that's what I named it.
I picked it up by the riverside one day\nin the middle of a sunshower, and we've\nbeen living together ever since.
Sam's real smart—it understands when\nI talk, and can even play board games!
And it's never annoying—unlike people.\nJust being around it calms me down.
You hungry, Sam?\nHere, have some nougat.
Yeah! We have nougat with nuts\nin the morning, milk in the afternoon,\nand chocolate at night. We rotate.
You feed it three meals of NOUGAT\na day?! How dare you push your terrible\neating habits onto this poor creature!
What do you know? I mean, dogs can't\neat onions, so maybe Sam can't eat\nanything but nougat.

That's so preposterously far-fetched it
makes my head whirl! Take this pearl of
wise advice, young man, and find this
creature some actual food post-haste.

Your attitude is god-tier annoying.
Do you seriously believe you're right?
'Cause if so, you just rolled a natural
twenty on being totally unhinged.
I will not stand by and listen to YOU\nof all people spout such drivel.

You sit about feeling bad for yourself,
and on the rare occasions you speak,
naught but gloom flows out! Little wonder
you're so cut off from the world.
Oh yeah, like people enjoy having some\negocentric hag boss 'em around all the\ntime! Yak yak yak, that's you!
I absolutely HATE you, young man!\nI absolutely HATE you, lady!
Sorry, Sam. I gotta lie down for a while.
This festival is as ready as it'll ever be.\nNow we just have to wait for tomorrow.

Visitors from the Halidom, let us ensure
that tomorrow's festival is perfectly
enthralling for all! Until then, ta-ta!
Oho! Oho ho ho ho ho!
Sam? What are you doing here?!
Of course you are! Because who would\never choose to live with a stubborn\nblockhead with nougat for brains?
Well then, let us be off to my manor.\nOho! Oho ho ho ho ho!
The meal is ready, milady. As you\nrequested, we omitted the onions.
Behold, a full-course meal prepared by\nmy own skilled chef. Please do enjoy.
If you're picky, you won't grow up big and\nstrong. Here, try this high-grade beef.
Wonderful! Now when you're done eating,\nI'll give you a nice wash in the bath.
Ah, but that water was so nice.\nNow let us make our way to bed.
What's this? Have you not played enough?\nWell, I fear the hour is much too late now.
The festival is tomorrow; we must retire\nearly and then make sure everything is\nabsolutely perfect.
And it simply MUST be perfect.\nFor if not...I will... I wiiiill...
MAKE ME SOME SUMMER MEMORIES!\nKYAAAAA HA HA HA HA!
This turned out to be a lovely day.\nThe festival is sure to—
Ho there, Prince of the Halidom!
Have you perchance seen Sam?\nSam's gone! You gotta help me!
Wait, why are YOU looking for Sam?!
Because the beast stayed at my manor!\nBut when I woke up, it was gone.
Oh my gosh, you selfish KIDNAPPER!
You contrarian craven! Sam ran away\nbecause it couldn't stand YOU and\nyour sourpuss ways!
Hey, let's all calm down here.
Oh, but this is terrible! Terrible, I say!
Fiends have appeared in the southern\nwoods and are headed for the town!
Fiends in the southern wood?\nImpossible. We took care of that.
But they ARE there, as well\nas some strange fluffy creature.
If fiends are on the way to town,\nwe'll head out there and stop them.
